I ate here once, the food was okay, not as good as I expected (as I saw good reviews on google) but not bad. I didn’t have time to cook and wanted fast food, so ordered fried chicken online.  But I had a very bad experience with my order tonight. After I received a text that it’s ready for pickup, I spent 20 minutes going to Momo.  The inside is super crowded, no physical distance, half of the people without the mask, even the bartender’s mask was covering her jaw. If I didn’t order a pickup, I’d never walk in a place like this during COVID. I was wearing my PPE mask, so I walked quickly through the crowds.  But there is worse. They told me the order is cancelled. After I reach home, I noticed that they cancelled it 15 minutes after I ordered. You should not cancel your customer’s order and at the same time text them it’s ready for pickup.
Had the wings abit ago, they were the best wings I've ever had!! The bartenders are definitely a reason ide some back!!

Momo. Home of delicious boneless chicken and unfortunately a restaurant that I will never visit again. About a week ago I ordered some Japache noodles, I was eagerly awaiting them since it is one of my favorite meals. Unfortunately that eagerness was grossly misplaced emphasis on the word grossly because I found a hair in my noodles. Nothing disgusts me more than finding hairs in my food. I immediately tried to get a refund from the food ordering app that I used and I was denied because apparently for them it's ok to have hair in your food. I guess in this age of Corona we all need the extra keratin. Afterwards I started to feel ill due to the nastiness of my meal. I am exceedingly disappointed by my experience and do not recommend this establishment or order mela through Uber Eats.

I usually don’t even like fried chicken, but this isn’t anything like fast food or American fried chicken. This is quality. Every bite of the fried chicken is flavorful and spicy. It is delicious. There is no other place that cooks fried chicken like Momo does.

Upon arrival, I was left waiting for about 5 minutes with no acknowledgement from the staff who appeared to be busy talking to each other and some friends who were sitting at the bar. I was immediately disappointed by this unprofessionalism. After finally sitting down, our server told my wife and I that the chicken would tale about 20 minutes to prepare, so we ordered a 20 piece half and half wings. However, the chicken DID NOT take 20 minutes like we were told; it took about 35-40 minutes. Now, I don't mind waiting this long, especially for this chicken, which indeed was very good, but I was disappointed that I was told false information. All in all, yes, this place has good chicken, but going there isn't worth the unprofessional staff.

Don’t eat at momo!  I was so excited to eat here. Seeing that there was a restaurant nearby that was open late with food that looked good was a proposition that seemed to good to be true. Unfortunately, it was just that.  We went in for dinner around 6:45 and got a nice seat in the corner. We were greeted by who I think was our server(still not sure to this moment) and asked for some water to start. Realizing that happy hour was ending in just a few minutes we put in an order for 2 beers around 6:55, specifically mentioning that we wanted to put it in before 7 for the happy hour deal. Our server told us it was okay and walked away. We flagged her down a few minutes later and asked for 2 appetizers(also included in the happy hour) and she said she’d go ahead and put the order in. At 7:03 she returned asking again what our order was before saying “unfortunately, it’s way past 7 so we won’t be able to do happy hour”. This was infuriating!  Nevertheless, we tried to move forward with open minds. After we ordered our food our server rushed off before we were able to order drinks and she avoided eye contact for about 10 minutes. We were finally able to order our drinks and we remained optimistic. Our food came along with this nasty man(who we later found out was the manager)that seemed offended simply by our presence. He slammed our plates on the table and rushed off without a word. Still missing utensils, we sat in shock as to what had just happened.  Overall, the only saving grace was this fantastic gentleman named Josh. When no one else showed the slightest bit of care, he was there consistently checking to see if there was anything that he could do for us. We will never return however I wish that there could be more people in the industry like Josh.

I love Momo's Chicken & Jazz because it blends a low-key, arty audiophile atmosphere with with a friendly lack of pretension, amazing chicken wings with a special batter (among other Korean-influenced food options), good music, and good service. It's a little on the loud side due to room acoustics, but still a good place to grab a beer (pint or pitcher) or wine and enjoy some conversation (and the aforementioned wings, spicy or garlicky). They have a Korean liquor that is pretty tasty (try a flight with different flavors) - but careful, it will give you a serious buzz. Other than wings, I recommend the bulgogi sliders for a *very* light bite. The street tacos were OK, very messy to eat. The chicken skewers were surprisingly UNinspired by comparison with their other options, but if you like "plain" food, go for it. There is outdoor seating which is often unfilled.

I went to Momo this past weekend to celebrate a friend's birthday.  The entire experience was frustrating.  Our server was extremely slow, making it difficult to order drinks.  She was also unsure about whether they had or could make everything we tried to order.  Drinks were extremely overpriced (at least double what I'd expect anywhere else).  It took about 30 minutes to get my drink and another 30 minutes to pay by credit card when everyone in our party was annoyed and wanted to leave.  The server failed to bus the table, leaving dirty dishes in front of us.  We finally stacked them up for her and placed them at the end of the table, where they sat until we left.  This could have been a fun place if they would fix the service and drink prices (serve me two drinks at half the price).  As it is, I don't see why anyone would return.

I did not eat at MoMo's because I was very disappointed with the lack of gluten free choices.  When you hear how good the wings are, you want to experience the wings not a salad.  I hope they consider adding gluten free options that give a sense of the MoMo experience.

Talk about tasty! We were looking for good Asian food in the area and Yelp stumbled upon this treasure. MoMo Chicken was a totally new kind of cuisine than I've had before. Asian food in Bethesda is kind of lackluster usually, so I was certainly surprised to see this hip place pop up!  Pros: + Wings. + More Wings. + I'm really serious about the Wings. I'm a fan of wings just about anywhere, but now, I wish that all wings could be like these. We got both kinds: which were equally different, and equally delicious. + Tasty bar food (I got divine Pork Buns) + Amazing atmosphere. Cool and Industrial. + Multiple TVs for Football season.  Cons: - It is definitely pricy. You'll end up buying lots of wings. - Same-old Bethesda parking situation. Look for a garage, or you'll get a headache.  Go for the wings, stay for the rest. MoMo chicken is going to become my new lunch spot pretty quickly. I just better watch my wallet!

My boyfriend and I have gotten take out from here once or twice before but decided to eat in yesterday.  (1-15-15)  The bar staff was friendly and courteous.  The food here is amazing and we will definitely be making more frequent trips in!  The soy ginger wings are amazing!!

The happy hour specials are very reasonable and the staff are great and friendly. The food is very tasty and always prepared well. The kitchen seems to be running well. I'd give them 5 stars except for the sports and news focus of the televisions. They really should put something on the TV's that is enjoyable, like maybe a movie marathon or Orphan Black or even a music video YouTube feed or something.
Great food and service. Really enjoyed. I love MoMo :)

We are passing through the DC area and found this place looking for dinner and live music.  We called and they don't have the live music yet but coming within a week or two as they are new.  That night we chose not to go, but thought the menu sounded interesting.  We stopped in today to catch the US world cup game before going hiking, as the menu sounded so interesting.  We had wings and fried chicken breast  (chicken strips) of both choices as our apps.  Don't order the pickels if you have an app, they are included.  The breading and sauces were great.  I lean towards the wings, but you can't go wrong either way.  I couldn't spell what I had, but it was a beef dish and my GF had the Tofu.  The serving sizes were large and reasonably priced.  I wish we were in town longer to go again, but it will be a definite stop on our next trip.  I can only imagine how great the dinners are.  Then with the live music this will be a home run!  Great Job!
